Package grafiosch.gtnet

Enum Class GNetCoreMessageCode

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<GNetCoreMessageCode>
grafiosch.gtnet.GNetCoreMessageCode
All Implemented Interfaces:
GTNetMessageCode, Serializable, Comparable<GNetCoreMessageCode>, Constable
public enum GNetCoreMessageCode extends Enum<GNetCoreMessageCode> implements GTNetMessageCode
Core protocol message codes for GNet peer-to-peer communication. This enum defines the fundamental protocol messages (codes 0-54) that are part of the GNet library. Application-specific message codes (60+) should be defined in separate enums that implement GTNetMessageCode.

Message Code Ranges

  • 0: Ping/health check
  • 1-4: Handshake protocol
  • 10-13: Server list exchange
  • 20-28: Status announcements (offline, maintenance, discontinued)
  • 30-34: Admin-to-admin messaging
  • 50-54: Data exchange negotiation
  • 60+: Reserved for application-specific messages
